---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | adi" description="About adi-param and this technical blog.">
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Hi, I’m Adi.</h1>
    <p>
      I’m a cybersecurity, cloud security, and DevSecOps engineer focused on
      securing cloud platforms, production systems, and large-scale digital
      services.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-main">
      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I have 13 years of experience across cybersecurity governance, cloud
        security, DevSecOps, secure SDLC, infrastructure security, incident
        response, and production reliability. My work has spanned regulated
        environments and enterprise platforms across Singapore and India.
      </p>
      <p>
        I currently work as a Senior Cloud Security and DevSecOps Engineer at
        Minden.ai in Singapore, where I support the yuu Rewards Club platform
        and its partner ecosystem. My work includes SOC implementation, cloud
        security controls, secure partner integrations, Okta SSO, Kubernetes
        security, vulnerability management, observability, and incident response.
      </p>

      <h2>What I work on</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Cloud and Kubernetes security across AWS and Azure environments</li>
        <li>Security operations, detection use cases, and incident response</li>
        <li>DevSecOps, secure SDLC, CI/CD security, and vulnerability management</li>
        <li>Infrastructure as Code with Terraform and GitOps workflows</li>
        <li>Observability, reliability, and production cost optimisation</li>
        <li>Secure partner integrations and enterprise access controls</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Certifications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>CISSP - Certified Information Systems Security Professional</li>
        <li>Certified Kubernetes Security Specialist (CKS)</li>
        <li>Microsoft Certified Azure Solutions Architect Expert</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why I write</h2>
      <p>
        This site is a place for practical technical notes: concepts that are
        worth remembering, architecture patterns that show up repeatedly, and
        troubleshooting explanations that benefit from being written down
        clearly.
      </p>
      <p>
        The posts are sourced from Markdown files in my repositories, so the
        writing stays close to the notes and examples I maintain while learning
        or working through a topic.
      </p>
    </div>

